		"description": "API documentation for User Authentication and Management.\n\n### Response Structure\nAll responses follow this format:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success|error\",\n  \"code\": 1xxx (Success) | 4xxx (Client Error) | 5xxx (Server Error),\n  \"message\": \"Human readable message\",\n  \"payload\": { ... } // Optional data\n}\n```\n\n### Status Codes\n- **1000**: Success General\n- **1001**: User Registered\n- **1002**: Login Successful\n- **4000**: Invalid JSON\n- **4002**: Invalid Credentials\n- **4003**: Invalid Email\n- **4004**: Invalid Password\n- **4005**: Invalid Username\n- **4006**: User Exists\n- **5000**: Internal Server Error",
